###
### TESTING NOTES:
### 
### EXPECTED SUCCESS FLOWS:
### 1. Create quotation (draft) → Send email → Status becomes 'sent' 
### 2. Sent quotation → Update status to 'accepted' → Convert to invoice
### 3. Draft quotation → Approve (if requiresApproval=true) → Send email
### 4. Any quotation → Generate shareable link → Access publicly
### 5. Multiple quotations → Bulk operations (status update, approve, delete)
###
### EXPECTED VALIDATION FAILURES:
### - Missing required fields (companyId, clientId, quotationTitle, items)
### - Invalid date formats or due date before date
### - Negative quantities or rates
### - Empty items array
### - Invalid status transitions (e.g., rejected → accepted)
### - Invalid email formats
### - Invalid MongoDB ObjectIds
###
### STATUS TRANSITION RULES:
### draft → [sent, draft]
### sent → [accepted, rejected, expired, draft]  
### accepted → [accepted, converted]
### rejected → [rejected]
### expired → [expired, draft]
### converted → [converted]
###
### BUSINESS RULES:
### - Only draft quotations can be deleted
### - Only accepted quotations can be converted to invoices
### - Quotations with requiresApproval=true must be approved before sending
### - Email sending auto-updates draft status to sent
### - Conversion auto-updates accepted status to converted
###
